The paper discusses a mobile agent network, specifically a multi-unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV) system, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The focus of the paper is on optimizing energy consumption, which involves communication and computation, making it relevant to the networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) category. The use of UAVs also suggests a potential fit for the robotics (cs.RO) category. The paper also discusses self-organizing networks and hierarchical clustering, which are topics relevant to the systems and control (cs.SY) category. Finally, the use of data aggregation and optimization techniques suggests a potential fit for the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) category.
